    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-16T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-16T05:00:00-05:00" n="434"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/3019: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-16T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 16, 1918—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 17—8:24 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Chinese Postal Administration wishes to acquire German post office in Legation
                    quarters. As this question comes under the cancelation of the 1901 protocol
                    between China and Germany, my colleagues consider with me that it must be
                    subordinated to arrangements to be reached at the Peace Conference. Similar
                    telegrams went to British, French and Japanese Governments. I request your
                    instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
